":"1152","1150":"1150","1172":"1172","England":"England, United Kingdom","Hellens Manor, Much Marcle, Herefordshire, England":"Much Marcle, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Hackluyt was born about 1178, in England, United Kingdom, her father, Leonard Hackluyt, was 29 and her mother, Mrs. Leonard Hackluyt, was 28. She had at least 1 son with John Walwyn I."},"et":{"Abt 1178–":"umbes 1178–Surnud","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","1172–Male":"1172–Surnud","1197–Male":"1197–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1152–Female":"1152–Surnud","Abt 1178":"umbes 1178","1178":"1178","1197":"1197","1152":"1152","1150":"1150","1172":"1172","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hellens Manor, Much Marcle, Herefordshire, England":"Much Marcle, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1178–":"noin 1178–Kuollut","1178–Female":"1178–Kuollut","1172–Male":"1172–Kuollut","1197–Male":"1197–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1152–Female":"1152–Kuollut","Abt 1178":"noin 1178","1178":"1178","1197":"1197","1152":"1152","1150":"1150","1172":"1172","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hellens